{"word":"H5274 - נָעַל - nâʻal - naw-al' - Bolt","slug":"H5274","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">נָעַל</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>nâʻal"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>naw-al'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Bolt"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E0;&#x05E2;&#x05DC; - na&#x0302;&#x201B;al</b> - <i>naw-al'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>fasten</i> up, that is, with a bar or cord; hence (denominatively from <a href=\"#/H5275\">H5275</a>), to <i>sandal</i>, that is, furnish with slippers: - bolt, inclose, lock, shod, shut up."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4514\">H4514</a>, <a href=\"#/H4515\">H4515</a>, <a href=\"#/H5275\">H5275</a>"}]}